commits.message: Fix wildcard include/exclude fields not matching `id`.
Add support for `nest` and `merge` reference include strategy.

Merge pull request #1341 from happy-san/reference_includes

Include reference document by merging or nesting.

pull_request.title: Include reference document by merging or nesting.
pull_request.body:
## Change Summary
Adds the ability to choose between `merge` and `nest` reference include strategies. Syntax for reference include:
 `$<reference_collection_name>( <field_names> : <include_strategy>)  as <alias>`

If the following is the document of the collection being searched,
```json
{
  "foo": 1
}
```
and this is the reference document,
```json
{
  "bar": 2,
  "baz": 3
}
```
with `merge` strategy, the resulting document will be:
```json
{
  "foo": 1,
  "bar": 2,
  "baz": 3
}
```
with `nest` strategy, the resulting document will be:
```json
{
  "foo": 1,
  "alias": {
    "bar": 2,
    "baz": 3
  }
}
```

issue.title: Option to use phrase-search synonyms that only return exact synonym matches
issue.body:
## Description

When adding synonyms that contain more than one word, the search ends up matching/highlighting the separate words. For example I created these synonyms: billy corgan, lead singer, frontman.

Querying "billy corgan" returns documents that contain both the words "lead" and "singer", but I expected that the synonyms should return exact matches only (e.g. only documents that contain the phrase "lead singer").

## Steps to reproduce
I tried using phrase synonyms with and without quotes but all of them gave the same result.
"synonyms": ["\"billy corgan\"", "\"lead singer\"", frontman]
"synonyms": ["billy corgan", "lead singer", frontman]
"synonyms": [billy corgan, lead singer, frontman]

## Metadata

**Typesense Version**:  v0.26.0.rc25

**OS**: Typesense Cloud
